->>> REGISTER_METHODS
@node REGISTER_METHODS "New Methods"

   @{b}set(@{"tag" link REGISTER_TAGS}, value)@{ub}

      By calling this method it's possible to change attributes
      at runtime. You can use all tags with the S flag set.
      This method can also be used before the GUI is created and when
      the window is closed.
      Value is a LONG and contains the argument for the used tag.
      @{FG fill}
      Example:
      DEF r:PTR TO register
      ...
      NEW r.register([PLA_Register_Titles, ['One','Two'], TAG_DONE])
      ...
      r.set(PLA_Register_Disabled, TRUE)
      ...
      @{FG text}

   @{b}value,check:=get(@{"tag" link REGISTER_TAGS})@{ub}

      This method is the counterpart to set. All tags with G flag
      can be used. Argument is the tag you want to get. Return values
      are the requested value and as second a boolean value. So if
      check is FALSE the used tag can't be get.

      @{FG fill}...
      value,check:=r.get(PLA_Register_Disabled)
      ...@{FG text}

      After this:
       value=TRUE
       check=TRUE

      But if you try:

      @{FG fill}...
      value,check:=r.get(PLA_Register_Titles)
      ...@{FG text}

      Then you get this:
       value:=-1
       check:=FALSE


   @{b}draw()@{ub}              @{FG shine}@{i}/* Private */@{ui}@{FG text}

   @{b}drawRegister()@{ub}      @{FG shine}@{i}/* Private */@{ui}@{FG text}

@endnode
-><<

->>> REGISTER_TAGS
@node REGISTER_TAGS "Tags"
 The letters [ISG] show you when the tags can be used.
 I = @{"Initalisation" link REGISTER_CONSTRUCTOR}
 S = @{"Set Method" link REGISTER_METHODS}
 G = @{"Get Method" link REGISTER_METHODS 20}


   @{FG shine}PLA_Register_Disabled@{FG text}  [ISG]

      Disable or enable a gadget. Setting this tag causes the
      gadget to become disabled, it gets a ghost pattern and
      doesn't respond to user input any longer.


   @{FG shine}PLA_Register_ActivePage@{FG text}  [ISG]

      Set (or get) the active page of the register.
      The value may range from 0 to number of titles-1.

      Or you can use these special values instead of numbers.

         PLV_Register_ActivePage_First
         PLV_Register_ActivePage_Last
         PLV_Register_ActivePage_Next
         PLV_Register_ActivePage_Prev


   @{FG shine}PLA_Register_Titles@{FG text}  [I..]

      List of strings describing the titles of your register.
      This tag MUST be set! Empty lists are also NOT allowed and will
      raise the @{"exception TITL" link REGISTER_EXCEPTIONS}. Empty strings were handled without
      problems.

      @{FG fill}Example:
      PLA_Register_Titles, ['Page1', 'Page2', 'Page3'],
      @{FG text}

   @{FG shine}PLA_Register_ActionHook@{FG text}  [I..]

      If you want to react on all changes, made by user input AND the
      set method, you can use this tag.
      Argument for this tag is a pointer to a installed hook.

      This tag will be called whenever the active page will be changed.

      The hook function will be called with 3 arguments:
         - pointer to your hook function
         - pointer to the register object
         - number of the active page.
       @{FG fill}
       Example:
       PROC actionhook(hook:PTR TO hook, obj:PTR TO register, activepage)
         ...
       ENDPROC
       @{FG text}

@endnode
